.TH SHELL 1 "April 2023" "Unix User Manual"
.SH NAME
shell \- a simple shell program in C
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
The shell is a simple command-line interpreter that reads commands from the user and executes them. It supports executing external commands with command-line arguments, as well as implementing the built-in commands 'env' and 'exit'.
.PP
The shell provides the following features:
.TP
o
Execute external commands with command-line arguments
.TP
o
Implement the 'env' built-in command to print the environment variables
.TP
o
Implement the 'exit' built-in command to terminate the shell
.TP
o
Support interactive mode (reading commands from the terminal) and non-interactive mode (reading commands from a file or pipe)
.SH "BUILT-IN COMMANDS"
.TP
.B env
Print the environment variables to the standard output.
.TP
.B exit
Terminate the shell process.
.SH LIMITATIONS
The shell has several limitations:
.TP
o
It does not handle input/output redirection or piping.
.TP
o
It does not support complex command syntax (e.g., parentheses, logical operators).
.TP
o
It does not implement any advanced features like aliases, history, or tab completion.
.TP
o
Error handling and memory management could be improved.
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
The shell was written by [Your Name].
.SH "SEE ALSO"
sh(1), bash(1)